Even though it may sound condescending when someone tells you to “shake it off,” there is actually great wisdom in this cliche. When a mammal experiences a traumatic event, their instincts guide them to find a safe place to shake. This shaking allows the animal to release the emotional reaction to whatever just transpired. We humans can also greatly benefit from this type of somatic release. So often we hold our traumas in our bodies, which creates chronic pain, injury, and illness. Somatic shaking is a therapeutic practice to help release stagnate emotions and trauma that has been stored in the body, providing the practitioner with an increased sense of mental clarity, joy, and personal peace.  Come to the somatic shakefest @sidestreamstudio for the solstice shake yo!

Toni is going to be performing a bunch of pieces at the March 11th show!!!! 

“The first piece, "I want to Poke your Buttons" is about our collective obsession with our phones. We use smartphones to connect us to the world, but they often disconnect us from ourselves and our surroundings. The phone is personified and represents being a "plaything" for the pleasures of others. The 2nd piece entitled, "Running from Wolves" is a dance about how the young female body is treated like prey to be hunted by rape culture. It explores the loneliness of feeling like an object meant to be captured. The 3rd piece is called "Connecting to You Through Disdain for Them." This dance looks at group dynamics and conformity - how people often create community through making others the enemy. It dives into the idea of identity and deeply fearing those that are different.”

Toni Nagy, the vibrant comedian, dancer, and filmmaker, is the creative force behind Brattleboro’s SideStream Studio. With over a decade of teaching movement classes and developing “Gyration Nation” at her studio, Toni’s fusion of dance and social consciousness activism has made her a New England performance fixture. So I had a rough weekend - emotionally draining and chaotic. I think it had been about a year since I last cried, and the problem with that is once I start, my tears are endless. My rage is volcanic. My sadness an abyss of darkness I get lost in. Maybe it’s self-pity or maybe it’s my primal wound? This unresolved scab that I keep thinking is healed, yet so easily bleeds out when picked. I wallowed a lot, and released what felt like a feral beast. Sigh. Just a humbling reminder of how far I still have to go. How raw I really am. How much things bother me that I wish didn’t. Anyway, there is always beauty in the mayhem. My kid was so supportive and kind to me. Knew exactly what to do. She gave me a hug and let me find comfort in her arms. I am forever grateful to her for showing me so much empathy and kindness when I felt so broken. I tried to pretend I was fine and nothing was wrong, so as not to burden a 13 year old kid, but she saw through my armor and gave the space to just be myself and weep. Anyway… hope you’re all well.  I am sending all my love to you and everyone in the world who suffering- which is a fuck ton of people - and that makes me wanna cry all over again.

JOIN US FOR A THRILLING NIGHT OF BURLESQUE AT SIDESTREAM!!! ❤️‍🔥🤘 SideStream Studio presents “Revive The Dead Inside,” a night of Burlesque to awaken your spirit during the depth of winter on Friday, January 26th at 7pm at the studio HQ in the Cotton Mill Building! Tickets are available at the door and online at www.sidestreamstudio.com for only $10.

Local Burlesque star Francesca Bourgault (aka Patty Cake) and SideStream Studio owner Toni
Nagy (aka Tony’s Bologna) are not only producing the show but will also be performing work
that is guaranteed to have your jaws dropped and eyes wide. The curation of the show focuses on local performers who not only entertain, but also provoke, prod, and play with the aperture of perception. These artists are not only talented in their craft of movement, but also with their wisdom of expression. The beauty of burlesque is beyond the physical, it’s an art form designed to decorate our desires - undressing our assumptions while stripping us of our conventions.

The show’s title, “Revive The Dead Inside” reminds us that even during these frigid New England nights, there is sensuality and beauty lurking in the shadows of darkness. It is a show that will explore the gruesome and inspiring possibilities of coming back from the brink. Each performance will excavate the fertile soil of our collective soul journey as we exhume the longing of human connection. 

Together, performers and audience will create a sacred alchemy that will be the medicine we
need to make it through the winter. Bring all the feelings! Come be yourself with us while we
reveal ourselves to you.

After the show there will be refreshments available as well as time and space for collective
processing. One of the most rewarding parts of live performance is talking about the show! At
SideStream Studio we believe that art is entrenched in life, and it’s crucial to create containers
to hold us while we pontificate, ponder, and play together.
